e_none=True` to omit null values | Unit test: None values not written to YAML | 0.5h |\n59: | 4.3.7 | Implement `update_metadata()` for load-update-save cycle | Unit test: updates applied and persisted to file | 1h |\n60: \n61: **Deliverable:** Core CRUD operations for metadata persistence.\n62: \n63: **Files:**\n64: - `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` - MetadataService class\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## ST-4.4 — MetadataService Workspace Validation\n69: \n70: ### Tasks\n71: \n72: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n73: |---|------|--------------|------|\n74: | 4.4.1 | Implement `validate_workspace()` checking workspace exists and is directory | Unit test: non-existent path raises ValueError, file path raises ValueError | 0.5h |\n75: | 4.4.2 | Implement `validate_workspace()` dispatching to language-specific validators | Unit test: python calls _validate_python_workspace, java calls _validate_java_workspace | 0.5h |\n76: | 4.4.3 | Implement `_validate_python_workspace()` requiring at least one *.py file | Unit test: workspace with .py passes, without raises ValueError | 0.5h |\n77: | 4.4.4 | Implement `_validate_java_workspace()` requiring pom.xml | Unit test: workspace with pom.xml passes, without raises ValueError | 0.5h |\n78: \n79: **Deliverable:** Workspace validation for Python and Java agents.\n80: \n81: **Files:**\n82: - `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` - validation methods\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## ST-4.5 — MetadataService Default Metadata Creation\n87: \n88: ### Tasks\n89: \n90: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n91: |---|------|--------------|------|\n92: | 4.5.1 | Implement `_create_default_metadata()` inferring agent_name from directory name | Unit test: /path/to/my-agent → agent_name=\"my-agent\" | 0.5h |\n93: | 4.5.2 | Implement `_infer_entrypoint()` for Python workspaces | Unit test: finds main.py, app.py, server.py in priority order | 1h |\n94: | 4.5.3 | Implement `_infer_entrypoint()` defaulting to \"python main.py\" when no candidate found | Unit test: returns \"python main.py\" when no files exist | 0.5h |\n95: | 4.5.4 | Implement `_infer_entrypoint()` for Java workspaces returning \"java -jar app.jar\" | Unit test: returns \"java -jar app.jar\" for Java language | 0.5h |\n96: | 4.5.5 | Ensure `_create_default_metadata()` creates valid AgentMetadata with required fields | Unit test: created metadata passes AgentMetadata.model_validate() | 0.5h |\n97: \n98: **Deliverable:** Automatic metadata inference from workspace contents.\n99: \n100: **Files:**\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 317. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService and Data Models\n\n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — AgentMetadata Model Enhancement\n\n### Tasks\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 4.1.1 | Add `model_config` to `AgentMetadata` with `populate_by_name=True`, `validate_assignment=True`, `extra='forbid'` | Unit test: extra fields raise ValidationError | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.2 | Add field `pack_timestamp: Optional[str]` with description \"ISO timestamp of pack operation\" | Unit test: field serializes/deserializes correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.3 | Add field `dockerfile_generated: Optional[bool]` with description \"Whether Dockerfile was generated\" | Unit test: field serializes/deserializes correctly | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.4 | Verify `language` validator accepts lowercase/uppercase, rejects invalid values | Unit test: \"Python\"→\"python\", \"invalid\" raises ValueError | 0.5h |\n| 4.1.5 | Verify `build_mode` validator accepts lowercase/uppercase, rejects invalid values | Unit test: \"Local\"→\"local\", \"invalid\" raises ValueError | 0.5h |","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/cli/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775897567556,"end":1775897567565}}}}
